		<td><b>Strange Port on the FDS RAM Adapter</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have noticed that there is this strange 10-pin port on the back of the FDS RAM Adapter.  This port exists in addition to the cable coming out of the RAM adapter that goes to the Disk System.  What was it used for, if anything?  A port for a slave drive, perhaps?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


